@4400 = ~Greetings. What treasures do you seek? I can offer you all legendary weapons—or the common relics of battle.~
@4401 = ~Give me the legendary weapons.~
@4402 = ~Give me the other weapons.~
@4403 = ~Give me the useful stuff.~
@4404 = ~Nothing today.~
@4405 = ~The world trembles for a heartbeat as small objects appear in your pack.~
@4406 = ~I’ve carried steel and blood on my hands for too many years... I want it to end. No more battles. No more killing.~
@4407 = ~Then lay down your weapon, brave one, and let the weight of war drift away like leaves upon a gentle current. The Mother of Groves does not judge the past—only the courage to choose stillness now.~
@4408 = ~So... let this tool of destruction rest. May my hands learn to heal instead of harm.~
@4409 = ~Eldath smiles upon your choice. Drink of Her blessed waters and walk on unburdened, with soft moss to cradle every step.~
@4410 = ~I feel... relieved...~
@4411 = ~A word with you, <PRO_RACE>. I see your weapons. Though I may not understand it, I can tell you cannot yet part with those you bear—at least not all of them. Others, perhaps, you could.~
@4412 = ~What do you mean by that?~
@4413 = ~Could you perhaps be a little less cryptic?~
@4414 = ~That sounds interesting.~
@4415 = ~I have no interest in this conversation. Farewell.~
@4416 = ~As you wish. Farewell.~
@4417 = ~It is rare that people like you pass through here—those who do not seek peace, but simply move on. You have seen many battles, of that I am sure. And you have collected many weapons whose former owners are no longer among the living.~
@4418 = ~You gather these weapons, sell them, and a new hand wields them to bring more death and suffering. It does not have to be so—not anymore.~
@4419 = ~If you were to bring all the weapons you have gathered here, they would harm no one again. In Eldath’s embrace, they shall be kept safe. It costs you nothing—you will still keep your own arms. But those you no longer need, leave them here.~
@4420 = ~Hah! Strip myself of spoils after battle? Ye ask a warrior’s folly.~
@4421 = ~You want to take all the weapons I find from my enemies?~
@4422 = ~What do I get in return?~
@4423 = ~Not all weapons—that would be more than even our sacred grove could bear. No, I mean the special ones, the unique ones. Those that have been swung in hundreds of battles, that have taken hundreds of lives. Bring such weapons here, and Eldath will bless you.~
@4424 = ~That... that sounds right. So much pain lingers in these blades. To put them to rest would be a kindness.~
@4425 = ~A wise proposal. Far too many weapons of dread pass from hand to hand, leaving only grief behind.~
@4426 = ~Yes, splendid. Let us all hand our power to the shrubbery. Truly, a masterstroke of silly strategy.~
@4427 = ~What weak sentiment. Weapons are meant to kill. I will not coddle blades that thirst for blood.~
@4428 = ~Uh. I dunno. I kind of like collecting weird, dangerous weapons. Makes me feel sparkly.~
@4429 = ~Blades thirst for blood, but even thirst can be slaked. To trade the clamor of battle for the hush of leaves...how sweet the verse.~
@4430 = ~One less blade sowing bloodshed—such is a gain for the balance. I will not stand against it.~
@4431 = ~In the harmony of the grove, the echoes of steel may be quieted at last. This is well.~
@4432 = ~I never would have guessed you deal in weapons.~
@4433 = ~Selling those weapons is how I make my living!~
@4434 = ~I cannot give you gold. But Eldath’s blessing is yours to take. With each weapon you surrender, she will grace you—granting you life and vitality beyond what killing alone could bring. With every blade you give up, you grow and thrive, even as others will *not* die by it anymore.~
@4435 = ~One less weapon, more life for you—that is Eldath’s bargain.~
@4436 = ~Which weapons exactly are we talking about?~
@4437 = ~You must be clearer about what I gain from this trade.~
@4438 = ~Weapons take life. Eldath gives life. If you give up a weapon, your life force will increase—a little more with each one surrendered.~
@4439 = ~Not a chance!~
@4440 = ~You will know them—the weapons that bear a name. A named weapon has claimed many lives. Such weapons will earn you Eldath’s blessing.~
@4441 = ~And those that have already become legend will grant you even greater vitality. So, what do you say?~
@4442 = ~Let's see if I have any weapons to offer Eldath.~
@4443 = ~I will think on it.~
@4444 = ~If this brings honor to Eldath, I shall gladly leave a blade or two behind.~
@4445 = ~I ask no more of you. Whenever you find a blade you will not wield yourself, think of Eldath—and take the chance to carry peace into the world. Farewell, <PRO_RACE>.~
@4446 = ~Greetings, <RACE>. Have you come to lay down your arms and receive the blessing of the Goddess?~
@4447 = ~What is this place?~
@4448 = ~Who are you?~
@4449 = ~I think I'll be going now.~
@4450 = ~I have weapons I’d like to lay to rest here.~
@4451 = ~Remind me, how was it again with the weapons I was to give you?~
@4452 = ~Your High Priest has sent me. I am to collect a carafe of Eldath’s sacred water.~
@4453 = ~The sacred water? Of course. Here it is — handle it with care, for it is as precious as the peace it brings.~
@4454 = ~I am a spirit bound to this grove. Long ago, Eldath’s touch calmed my frightened heart, and since then I serve as her gentle warden here. My soul is tied to its waters and the quiet breath of Eldath herself.~
@4455 = ~This is Eldath’s sacred grotto, where absolute peace prevails.~
@4456 = ~Here, many brave warriors have chosen to abandon their trade and follow the path of peace instead. Do you see the many weapons? Each one once belonged to a soul whose life was shaped by war and bloodshed—until they laid down their arms here and chose a different path.~
@4457 = ~All these weapons just thrown aside? So much steel, wasted... I can’t decide if it’s inspiring or foolish.~
@4458 = ~Peace is well and good—until the next pack of bandits shows up. Then what? Sing them to death?~
@4459 = ~A sword keeps you alive. Giving it up? That’s as good as digging your own grave.~
@4460 = ~That’s... admirable. To turn away from war takes more courage than swinging a blade ever could.~
@4461 = ~Have you come to lay down your weapons here as well, in the name of peace?~
@4462 = ~Tempus forbid, no!~
@4463 = ~To each their own, but I prefer keeping my weapon close at hand.~
@4464 = ~If I could, I would... but I’m not ready yet.~
@4465 = ~Let’s just hope none of them regret leaving their blades behind someday.~
@4466 = ~You don’t mind if I take a look at those weapons, do you? Maybe one or two could still be of use to me.~
@4467 = ~Peace is never forced here. Whether you hold a blade or set it down, only your heart can choose its path.~
@4468 = ~These weapons have already tasted blood. Whether they lie here or in your hands makes little difference to the past. Peace cannot be forced on the unwilling.~
@4469 = ~Do you perhaps keep any special weapons here—ones I might put to use?~
@4470 = ~Then I’ll take a look around, see if anything’s worth keeping.~
@4471 = ~A single blade among these still hums with ancient grief. It carries the weight of old vows, sworn in battles long past. If you are truly set on walking a path against the dead, it may answer your call. Perhaps it waits for someone bold enough to wield it once more.~
@4472 = ~Could you give it to me?~
@4473 = ~No, not yet. You are not ready for such a burden. If fate wills it, it will one day rest in your grasp. Be patient... perhaps, in time, you'll be chosen to wield the blade.~
@4474 = ~Then I’ll prove myself, no matter what trials lie ahead.~
@4475 = ~If it’s waiting for someone bold and handsome, I think I’m already the best candidate, but let's wait.~
@4476 = ~Peace to you, traveler. May your path be soft beneath your feet.~
@4477 = ~Return when you have weapons you wish to lay to rest.~
@4478 = ~So, you wish to trade a weapon for a bit more of your life? Eldath accepts all offerings.~
@4479 = ~I’d like to give you a famous weapon.~
@4480 = ~I’d like to give you a legendary weapon.~
@4481 = ~It seems I carry no weapon that I could leave here.~
@4482 = ~Not now.~
@4483 = ~What do I gain from this?~
@4484 = ~You shall receive Eldath’s blessing — your life will grow a little stronger.~
@4485 = ~Could you be a bit more specific?~
@4486 = ~That’s all I wanted to know.~
@4487 = ~I’ve changed my mind and will be on my way now.~
@4488 = ~With each weapon surrendered, you’ll feel your life grow—just a little for a lesser blade, more for a legendary one. Only Eldath knows the true worth of each weapon that vanishes from the world.~
@4489 = ~Legendary blades have stirred armies and sundered vows. Which of these weapons will you lay down?~
@4490 = ~The Equalizer balanced nothing but corpses. Let the water end its argument.~
@4491 = ~Carsomyr’s zeal cuts too deep. I surrender it to stillness.~
@4492 = ~The Flail of Ages bound three tempests to war; unbind it here.~
@4493 = ~Crom Faeyr shook mountains; let it trouble roots and moss no more.~
@4494 = ~Soul Reaver drinks hope; I give it to waters that heal.~
@4495 = ~Blackrazor whispers of hunger. May the pool teach it silence.~
@4496 = ~I can’t stand Lilarcor's chatter anymore. Take it. If anyone can hush it, it’s you.~
@4497 = ~Celestial Fury’s thunder belongs to the sky, not to wandering hands.~
@4498 = ~I offer the Warblade—its edge has tasted enough blood.~
@4499 = ~Take the Silver Sword—may it claim no more minds or lives.~
@4500 = ~The Shortbow of Gesen—let its lightning sleep in peace.~
@4501 = ~Even Icingdeath’s chill should rest now.~
@4502 = ~Twinkle’s light can fade in peace here.~
@4503 = ~Even the Staff of the Magi can be laid to rest.~
@4504 = ~This blade calls itself the Doomed Loser. Let it vanish into still waters instead.~
@4505 = ~The Flayer Slayer has cleaved through horrors best left forgotten. Let Eldath’s waters wash its memory away.~
@4506 = ~Perhaps we should start over, then.~
@4507 = ~I changed my mind and will leave. Farewell.~
@4508 = ~Some battles leave wounds that no healer can close—save time and stillness.~
@4509 = ~By Eldath… a sword that flees after failure. What a cruel jest of the Abyss. Let it trouble no hands again.~
@4510 = ~A gleam that severed thought and fate; let it fade beneath still waters.~
@4511 = ~Storms belong to the sky, not the vein. The pool will quiet its spark.~
@4512 = ~A famed frost laid to thaw; may peace melt its legend to quiet.~
@4513 = ~Brightness is not always kindness; let gentler stars watch over it.~
@4514 = ~Great power stirs great tempests; here, it will know still waters.~
@4515 = ~Steel that fed on war should sleep, not sing. Let the grove still its hunger.~
@4516 = ~Endless balance sought through endless strife... let the water end the argument.~
@4517 = ~Holy or not, such a sword has ended many lives. Be still now.~
@4518 = ~Shards of three tempests belong in one calm pool.~
@4519 = ~Strength that breaks mountains can also break the quiet. Lay it down.~
@4520 = ~A draught of despair clings to this steel. The moss will drink it away.~
@4521 = ~Hush. Your hunger will trouble the grove no longer.~
@4522 = ~Thunder belongs to the sky, not to mortal tempers. Sleep now.~
@4523 = ~Even in silence, I hear the chatter. The pool will teach you quiet.~
@4524 = ~The pool is ready for another burden of legend.~
@4525 = ~I have another legendary blade.~
@4526 = ~Perhaps we can start over.~
@4527 = ~A wise decision. Which magical weapons will you surrender?~
@4528 = ~The Skullcrusher belongs where skulls are safe. Take it.~
@4529 = ~The Hammer of Thunderbolts should thunder no more.~
@4530 = ~Let the Dwarven Thrower find stillness here.~
@4531 = ~The Boneblade has feasted on enough death. Keep it safe.~
@4532 = ~Take Blackblood—may it never taste life again.~
@4533 = ~The Blade of Searing shall burn no more flesh.~
@4534 = ~Azuredge can rest; its crusade is done.~
@4535 = ~I part with Heartseeker—no more hearts shall it find.~
@4536 = ~The Elven Court Bow belongs to memory, not to murder. Take it.~
@4537 = ~The Impaler has ended enough lives. Keep it where it can harm none.~
@4538 = ~I surrender the Spear of Withering—no more decay for the living.~
@4539 = ~Take Frostreaver—its cold bite ends here.~
@4540 = ~This Blade of Roses has stained too many proud hearts; I bring it to you now.~
@4541 = ~Here, take Stonefire. May its flames trouble no more hearts.~
@4542 = ~The Rifthome Axe split enough skulls in its time. It’s yours to keep from harm.~
@4543 = ~Dragon’s Bane has no place in a peaceful grove. I give it to you freely.~
@4544 = ~The Wave Halberd belongs to calmer tides. Let it rest here.~
@4545 = ~Ras was called by blood’s ghost; I set it free from summoning’s chain.~
@4546 = ~Pixie Prick sleeps with stolen breath; I return it to stillness here.~
@4547 = ~Named for murder’s hand, Cutthroat finds no welcome here. I surrender it gladly.~
@4548 = ~Spectral Brand tastes of undead sorrow; may its echo fade in the pool’s embrace.~
@4549 = ~Adjatha the Drinker fed on magic—let its thirst end under your watch.~
@4550 = ~The Sword of Chaos hurled fate blindly; I gift it to the roots of stillness.~
@4551 = ~Albruin was forged for hunts long past. I lay it down so nothing hunts here.~
@4552 = ~The Sword of flame split more than bodies. Let it cool in this hush.~
@4553 = ~Daystar cut through darkness—but light can blind as fiercely. This is its rest.~
@4554 = ~Betrayal’s short sword sits heavy in the soul. I leave it for still water’s healing.~
@4555 = ~Belm swung for vengeance. May its arc end in silent grace.~
@4556 = ~A dagger of venom finds no purchase here. I give it to the roots and let it rot in quiet.~
@4557 = ~I wish to part with Jhor the Bleeder—it has drawn enough blood in its time.~
@4558 = ~The Blade of the Elven Mycologist… its edge smells faintly of damp earth. May it return to the soil.~
@4559 = ~Mirage’s Edge—its shimmer cuts through more than steel. Let its illusions fade into peace.~
@4560 = ~Scolopendra's Spit… venomous, patient, and silent. I will not miss its company.~
@4561 = ~Good Luck, Honeysuckle… may its fortune bloom for another, far from the clash of blades.~
@4562 = ~Bard's Love Letter… words unspoken now whispered only by the bowstring.~
@4563 = ~Hammer of Powerful Yet Unlikely Blows… each strike a story, each miss an even better one.~
@4564 = ~I surrender False Pride—may humility drown its conceit.~
@4565 = ~Take this Skull Mace—its hunger for strength ends here.~
@4566 = ~Here—‘Flesh and Boils’. It belongs nowhere among the living.~
@4567 = ~The Meatshaper warps flesh with every blow. End it here.~
@4568 = ~‘Heads’—a coin turned killer. I give it to the pool.~
@4569 = ~‘Tails’—let the other half of this blade rest as well.~
@4570 = ~The Venom Slicer carries the Abyss in its bite. Take it.~
@4571 = ~This Bloodblade drips with the Lower Planes. Let it bleed out here.~
@4572 = ~The Rust Spreader corrupts all it touches—end its creeping rot.~
@4573 = ~This heart-shaped razor was made for butchery, not love—take it.~
@4574 = ~Blackbite has bitten enough in its time. Let the waters wash away its venom.~
@4575 = ~The Bonefang has crushed enough skulls. I think it’s time it found peace here.~
@4576 = ~The Astral Mace of Blasting should mark no more endings. Let it rest under Eldath’s gaze.~
@4577 = ~The Clockwork Blade of Venom has ticked its last strike. Let the gears wind down in peace.~
@4578 = ~Grubnuk’s Hand has clutched enough lives. I think it’s time it let go forever.~
@4579 = ~The Prismatic Scimitar has shone enough colors in battle. Time to let it fade into quiet waters.~
@4580 = ~The Air Hammer has cleared enough storms. Let the winds settle here.~
@4581 = ~Let bone be shielded by mercy, not broken by rage.~
@4582 = ~Boom becomes hush; may the sky forgive what the forge demanded.~
@4583 = ~A faithful tool of war can be faithful to peace.~
@4584 = ~Let marrow remember life, not cutting.~
@4585 = ~Let this bitter club be sweetened by stillness.~
@4586 = ~Fire forgets itself in water; so too shall this blade.~
@4587 = ~Even righteous edges can cut too deep. The grove will keep it gentle.~
@4588 = ~Pride cuts deeper than steel. The pool will teach this blade to be still.~
@4589 = ~A fallen paladin’s skull profaned… what horrors mortals make. Let mercy close its teeth forever.~
@4590 = ~A club of meat and acid… the Abyss mocks the body itself. Let the waters unmake this blight.~
@4591 = ~Sinew threaded with cruelty. Peace will not abide such stitching.~
@4592 = ~Wealth twisted into death… may the water cool its greed.~
@4593 = ~Two halves of one greed. Both will sink, and none shall drown by them again.~
@4594 = ~Tharzax’s poison has no voice in this grove. The waters will silence its sting.~
@4595 = ~Sap that keeps wounds from closing… abominations upon healing. Peace will close what this opened.~
@4596 = ~A blade that gnaws even its wielder… such misery belongs to the depths.~
@4597 = ~‘You cannot crush the heart that’s already missing’… such cruelty shall not echo here.~
@4598 = ~Let arrows stray from sorrow; may this bow learn gentleness at last.~
@4599 = ~An heirloom of grace turned grim—let the grove return it to grace.~
@4600 = ~A point made too often dulls the world. The waters will blunt it kindly.~
@4601 = ~Let blight unlearn its path; the pool remembers only growth.~
@4602 = ~Winter’s edge has no place in a summer grove.~
@4603 = ~A dragon’s fang should rest in still waters, not in fresh blood.~
@4604 = ~Even a giant’s strength can be laid to rest in the waters.~
@4605 = ~Even the stars fade into stillness in time.~
@4606 = ~Even time itself can be coaxed into stillness.~
@4607 = ~Even a troll’s grasp loosens when offered peace.~
@4608 = ~Even light can rest when the fight is done.~
@4609 = ~Even the wind grows weary and seeks calm.~
@4610 = ~Even steel may grow weary of blood. Let the moss claim it now.~
@4611 = ~Even mirages must rest when the light grows gentle. I will guard this blade until it dreams of battle no more.~
@4612 = ~Venom without a hand to guide it drips harmless into the earth.~
@4613 = ~Some luck is better sown than swung. Let the grove be its new keeper.~
@4614 = ~Let the wind carry its verses, not its arrows.~
@4615 = ~May its next tale be of peace, not shattering.~
@4616 = ~Then let its thirst be quenched forever, and its memory sink into still waters.~
@4617 = ~May the brightness of peace outshine any duel this blade once starred in.~
@4618 = ~From molten memory to the calm of stone and water.~
@4619 = ~Axes remember feuds long after the names are gone.~
@4620 = ~Let the flame that once burned dragons fade into silent ash.~
@4621 = ~A tide turned to killing is no tide for this grove.~
@4622 = ~Let the dead rest. No more summons.~
@4623 = ~Sleep should be mercy, not ambush.~
@4624 = ~Steel named for murder needs quiet most of all.~
@4625 = ~Let echoes return to silence.~
@4626 = ~Thirst for magic is still thirst. Be satisfied no more.~
@4627 = ~Chaos feeds on crowds. Here, it starves.~
@4628 = ~Hunters of the hidden often become what they fear. Rest now.~
@4629 = ~Fire in a hilt is still fire. The pool will cool it.~
@4630 = ~Light can blind as surely as it guides.~
@4631 = ~Let betrayal find no purchase here.~
@4632 = ~A quick hand learns patience, in time.~
@4633 = ~Venom loses its sting in still water.~
@4634 = ~The pool is ready for another burden.~
@4635 = ~I have another weapon to surrender.~
